&lt;pre&gt;Thanks for the review.
I have added pseudo-wpt test and reference to existing browser tests:&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Web Platform Tests or other automated test descriptionThe pseudo-wpt test
is implemented here
chrome/test/data/controlled_frame/webrequest_read.window.js. Command to run
it - `autoninja -C out/Default browser_tests &amp;&amp; out/Default/browser_tests
--gtest_filter=ControlledFrameWptBrowserTest.Run/webrequest_read` -
pseudo-wpt is a historical artifact of parent feature controlled frame.
More info is in the Web Platform Tests section
&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5199572022853632?gate=5134483605422080"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5199572022853632?gate=5134483605422080&lt;/a&gt; -
this test only supports `state=&quot;secure&quot;`, because an endpoint with invalid
certificate is not possible to use in the wpt environment. There's more
complete browser tests which covers all possible cases and states:
chrome/browser/extensions/api/web_request/web_request_apitest.cc
gtest_filter=ExtensionWebRequestApiTest.SecurityInfo*,
SecurityInfoBrokenWebRequestApiTest.*

