On Thu, Jan 8, 2026 at 3:24 PM Hubert Chao &lt;&lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="dbb3b8f5f5f59bb8b3a9b4b6b2aeb6f5b4a9bc"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;&gt; wrote:

&gt; *Contact emails*
&gt; &lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="deb6bdf0f0f09ebdb6acb1b3b7abb3f0b1acb9"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;,  &lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="fb988f93d5d5d5bb9893899496928e96d594899c"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt; &lt;&lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="aac2c9848484eac9c2d8c5c7c3dfc784c5d8cd"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; *Summary*
&gt; This is an enhancement to the Local Network Access(LNA) restrictions,
&gt; where we split the permission required from one Local Network Access
&gt; permission, into 2 separate permissions.
&gt;
&gt; Old permission name:
&gt; local-network-access
&gt;
&gt; New Permission names:
&gt; local-network (for LNA requests to IPs in the local address space)
&gt; loopback-network (for LNA requests to IPs in the loopback address space)
&gt;
&gt; The old permission names are kept as an alias and should continue to work
&gt; for permissions.query and Permissions Policy for the foreseeable future.
&gt;
&gt; See &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5152728072060928"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5152728072060928&lt;/a&gt; for an overview of
&gt; LNA;
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/cwu_RUmBpzY/m/JWenvGViCAAJ"&gt;https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/cwu_RUmBpzY/m/JWenvGViCAAJ&lt;/a&gt;
&gt; for the original LNA I2S, and
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WICG/local-network-access/issues/17"&gt;https://github.com/WICG/local-network-access/issues/17&lt;/a&gt; for a discussion
&gt; of splitting the permission and the naming of the new permissions.
