*Contact emails* &lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="ef878cc1c1c1af8c879d8082869a82c1809d88"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection" class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="197a6d71373737597a716b7674706c7437766b7e"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt; &lt;&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#1c747f3232325c7f746e737175697132736e7b"&gt;mailto:&lt;span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="a3cbc08d8d8de3c0cbd1cccecad6ce8dccd1c4"&gt;[email&#160;protected]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
*Summary* This is an enhancement to the Local Network Access(LNA) restrictions, where we split the permission required from one Local Network Access permission, into 2 separate permissions.
Old permission name: local-network-access
New Permission names: local-network (for LNA requests to IPs in the local address space) loopback-network (for LNA requests to IPs in the loopback address space)
The old permission names are kept as an alias and should continue to work for permissions.query and Permissions Policy for the foreseeable future.
See &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5152728072060928 for"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5152728072060928 for&lt;/a&gt; an overview of LNA;
&lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/cwu_RUmBpzY/m/JWenvGViCAAJ"&gt;https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/g/blink-dev/c/cwu_RUmBpzY/m/JWenvGViCAAJ&lt;/a&gt; for the original LNA I2S, and &lt;a rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WICG/local-network-access/issues/17"&gt;https://github.com/WICG/local-network-access/issues/17&lt;/a&gt; for a discussion of splitting the permission and the naming of the new permissions.
