&lt;pre&gt;I'm sorry, it's too late. Currently, the HTML spec 
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/canvas.html#dom-context-2d-letterspacing"&gt;https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/canvas.html#dom-context-2d-letterspacing&lt;/a&gt;&gt;

says

   1. 

   Let parsed be the result of parsing 
   &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-syntax/#parse-grammar"&gt;https://drafts.csswg.org/css-syntax/#parse-grammar&lt;/a&gt;&gt; the given value as 
   a CSS &lt;length&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-values/#lengths"&gt;https://drafts.csswg.org/css-values/#lengths&lt;/a&gt;&gt;.

So, I intent to implement the percentage unit support for 
context-2d-letterspacing separately at a later time.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Thank you.
